con:config.script: //Clearing Legacy Properties log.info("Clearing Legacy Project Properties") testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue("Pass_Word","") testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue("PIC_NUMBER","") testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue("TC_EventTrackingHTML","") testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue("Namespace","") testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue("IntegrationID","") testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue("ShipDate","") testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue("User_Id","") testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue("Environment","") testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue("IntegratorTxID","") testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue("ServiceEndpoint-SWSIM","") testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue("CSVHeader","") def nowTime = new Date().format("dd-MMM-yyyy'T'HH.mm.ss") log.info(nowTime) testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue("TestRunTime", nowTime) //log.info("Legacy Project Properties Cleared") // Importing New Project properties def projectPath = context.expand( '${#Project#OutPut_Logs_Directory}' ) def projpro = new Properties() def projectpathnew def propertyloc projectpathnew = projectPath.replace("\\", "/") propertyloc = projectpathnew.concat("/main.properties") new File(propertyloc).withInputStream { stem -> projpro.load(stem) } projpro.each { testRunner.testCase.testSuite.project.setPropertyValue(it.key, it.value) } log.info("Project Properties Imported Successfully")
